div.p:
The claim is made in the Totonicapan that the Lord gave the ancient leader of this group a
"present called Giron-Galgal," which guided the ancestors of the Indians across the ocean to
their new land. (Ibid.) This gift is comparable to the Liahona, which was given to Father Lehi by
the Lord to serve as a compass to guide his people from Jerusalem to America (1 Ne. 16:10,27;
1 Ne. 18:12;
D&C 17:1).
